gomodel:SYNGO_1347  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Electrophysiological characterisation of Na(v)1.1 expressed in sA-201 cells using WC patch-clamp.\n\nrule: NAS_MFCC-BP\nrationale:\nProtein has voltage-gated ion channel activity and is localized in the presynaptic membrane (show with high-resolution technique). The inference to term 'voltage-gated ion channel activity involved in regulation of presynaptic membrane potential (GO:0099508)' is trivial and non-controversial.\nPinf_CC:\n[P04774] SyNGO ID 1341 (PMID:18079688, EM). Experimental description: The cDNAs of the human NaV1.1 Na+ channel a subunit (hNaV1.1; GenBank sequence NM_006920.4) and of the human NaV1.2 Na+ channel a subunit (hNaV1.2; NM_021007) were provided by Dr. Jeff Clare (Glaxo- SmithKline, Stevenage, Herts, United Kingdom). The NaV1.1 clone is a shorter splice variant, with a deletion of 11 amino acids in the intracellular loop between DI and DII, which has already been used in several studies (Mantegazza et al., 2005; Rusconi et al., 2007; Cestele et al., 2008; Rusconi et al., 2009) and could be the predominant NaV1.1 variant expressed in brain (Schaller et al., 1992)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9425-2935" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_MF_1347" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

